parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Insufficient Rear Air Conditioning Air Flow
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of adequate air flow from the rear air conditioning vents can cause discomfort, heat stroke, and potentially life-threatening conditions for passengers, especially children, in the rear seats.
symptoms: Weak or slow air flow from the rear air conditioning vents
inability to feel the air flow
rear seats becoming extremely hot
especially when windows cannot be opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can lead to costly repairs, decreased vehicle performance, and potential environmental harm.
symptoms: Check engine light illuminates
diagnosis of catalytic converter failure
recommendation to replace both converters at a high cost.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Air Conditioning Evaporator Fan Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the rear air conditioning evaporator fan can cause the system to fail, leading to costly repairs and discomfort for passengers.
symptoms: Clogged evaporator vanes due to lack of air filter
failure of the rear air conditioning system
weak or no air flow from the rear vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Warning Light and Occupant Detection System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag warning light and occupant detection system can lead to incorrect airbag deployment, which can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard stays on
the passenger airbag warning light stays on even when someone is sitting in the seat
the airbag light blinks
and the vehicle cannot pass inspection due to the warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbags fail to deploy in an accident
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Worn or Warped Front Brake Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn or warped front brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate violently when braking, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes violently when braking
especially at high speeds (60 mph or more)
the brake pedal pulsates or vibrates
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise.
